description.value: Glazed composition shabti of Wahibrasaneith: as with all funerary figurines of the period, this superbly moulded shabti in a apple green glazed composition of the high official Wahibrasaneith, born to the lady Shepenbastet, wears a long wig with two lappets, in this case striped, and a plaited divine beard. In his hands, crossed over the chest, he holds a composite hoe and an adze for carrying out the agricultural tasks required of his dead master in the other world. The cord in his right hand leads to a small woven seed bag behind the left shoulder for carrying seed or harvested crops. The back pillar, once an essential element of stone standing statuary, is now present as a magical support. The hieroglyphic text around the body is the standardized Saite version of Chapter 6 of the 'Book of the Dead', the shabti formula which will bring the figure to life to work on its owners behalf.
